# Ethereum Community Hub Mauritius – Event Programming

Consistent programming is essential to maintaining an active and engaged community. The hub will run a combination of educational, social, and technical events.

---

# Monthly Meetups

Frequency: Once per month

Purpose:

• Introduce new members to Ethereum
• Share knowledge about blockchain technology
• Connect developers, students, and entrepreneurs

Typical agenda:

• Introduction to Ethereum topics
• Guest speakers from the Web3 ecosystem
• Community networking

Expected attendance: 20–30 participants.

---

# Developer Workshops

Frequency: Every 2 months

Focus topics:

• Solidity smart contract development
• Ethereum development tools
• Wallet integration and Web3 applications
• Open source contributions

These workshops will help participants move from learning about blockchain to actively building projects.

---

# Bootcamps

Frequency: Every 2 months

Bootcamps will provide deeper training sessions for students and developers interested in Ethereum development.

Topics may include:

• Blockchain fundamentals
• Smart contracts
• Decentralized applications (dApps)
• Ethereum ecosystem tools

---

# Hackathons

Frequency: Every 6 months

Hackathons will encourage participants to collaborate and build real-world solutions using Ethereum.

Goals:

• Encourage innovation
• Identify talented builders
• Create prototype Web3 projects

---

# NFT Creator Events

The hub will also organize sessions specifically for artists and creators.

Activities:

• NFT education workshops
• Artist onboarding sessions
• NFT exhibitions
• Collaboration with local creators

These activities aim to connect the creative economy in Mauritius with blockchain technology.
